parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the brake to malfunction, leading to loss of control, accidents, and risk to driver and passenger safety.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake caliper lies on the inside of the rim
extensive damage to the vehicle
tire
rim
suspension components
and brake components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive brake heat can cause brake failure, leading to loss of control, accidents, and risk to driver and passenger safety.
symptoms: The front brakes get excessively hot during normal stopping
even after replacing brake pads and rotors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent ABS activation can cause the vehicle to not stop as expected, leading to accidents, and risk to driver and passenger safety.
symptoms: The ABS intermittently comes on when brakes are being used under regular pressure
causing the vehicle to not stop as expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake wear sensor issues can cause the driver to be unaware of brake wear, leading to brake failure, loss of control, accidents, and risk to driver and passenger safety.
symptoms: The brake wear sensor is not installed
but the vehicle's parts department confirms it is needed
and the dealership advises to cut the wear sensor cable and install the brake pads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Front brake noise and slippage can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, and risk to driver and passenger safety.
symptoms: The front brakes make a whistling noise when activated
and slippage occurs in rainy conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause the vehicle to not stop as expected, leading to accidents, and risk to driver and passenger safety.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to stop when the brake pedal is depressed
and excessive force is required to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to inform the buyer about a brake safety recall can lead to accidents, and risk to driver and passenger safety.
symptoms: The dealer fails to inform the buyer about a brake safety recall
and the buyer is asked to drive the vehicle to the dealership despite a "do not drive" warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine damage, increased emissions, and potentially cause accidents due to oil leaks or engine failure.
symptoms: Oil level warning lights
oil sensor blinking
excessive oil consumption
oil leaks
engine burning oil.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the air pump control valve can cause increased tailpipe emissions, engine damage, and potentially lead to accidents due to loss of engine power.
symptoms: Check engine light
air system leak
primary engine water pump losing pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the intake manifold runner can cause the vehicle to suddenly enter limp mode, leading to hazardous situations due to sudden slowing.
symptoms: MIL light illuminating
diagnostics confirm failure of the intake manifold runner
vehicle entering limp mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent stalling can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs at stoplights or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling at stops
vehicle restarting
frequent stalling
unable to replicate issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Shaking and Check Engine Light
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine shaking and check engine light can indicate underlying engine problems, potentially leading to engine failure or accidents.
symptoms: EPC light
check engine light
car shaking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various warning lights to illuminate, rear-view camera malfunction, and airbag sensor errors, which can lead to accidents or distract the driver.
symptoms: Unknown warning lights illuminate
rear-view camera activates while the vehicle is in drive
passenger occupant airbag sensor flashes on and off without a passenger being seated
and unstated electrical failures while driving at various speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to turn off while in drive, leading to a significant safety hazard, as the vehicle can roll uncontrolled and strike a person or object.
symptoms: The vehicle can be turned off while in drive
with no extra signals (beeps
flashing lights
etc.)
and the vehicle will roll until the brake is applied or it comes to rest on a flat surface or against a hard object.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbag to deploy unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries, or fail to deploy in the event of a crash, putting occupants at risk.
symptoms: Airbag error warnings
concerns about airbag deployment while driving
and worries about airbag failure in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, as the radio/video monitor goes black and no sound, and the backup camera fails to engage.
symptoms: Radio/video monitor goes black and no sound
and the backup camera fails to engage after different periods of time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can cause a lack of warning to other drivers, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The horn is inoperable with the ignition in the off position.
